He added that the appellants failed to prove issues of over-voting when it could not produce authentic voters register to validate its claim.Justice Okoro added that the unanimous decision of the court delivered on 30 October 2019 was in total agreement with the verdict of the lower court which upheld and affirmed the election of Buhari.